gomodel:SYNGO_4941  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2a,b: CAR (gene CXADR) was consistently enriched in synaptosomes (but not detected in PSD) fractions from both mouse and human brain tissue.\n\nFigure 2c-f: immunofluorescence labeling of cultured hippocampal neurons showed partial co-localization of CAR (gene CXADR) with VGLUT and, to a lesser extend, VGAT suggesting presynaptic localization. Triple-staining for CAR, VGLUT and PSD95 (DLG4) confirmed localization of CAR at presynaptic terminals to postsynaptic densities.\n\n\"Together, these data demonstrate that CAR is preferentially expressed by neurons in the mouse brain, on the soma of cells in the SGZ of the DG, in the mossy fibers in the SLu, and in axons projecting from the entorhinal cortex. At the synapse, CAR is at the presynapse and undetectable at the postsynapse, suggesting that intercellular CAR-CAR interactions that predominate in epithelial cells are not occurring at the synapse.\"\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: For IHC/IF staining the author writes (From M+M): \"Goat anti-CAR Ab (R&D Systems). Two rabbit anti-CAR antibodies (Bethyl A302-847A and Atlas HPA003342) gave identical signals during immunofluorescence (IF) assay in wild-type (WT) and CAR-CNSKO mice.\"\n\nFrom M+M: \"Presynaptic and postsynaptic protein extracts from the hippocampi of control and CAR-CNSKO mice were used in immunoblotting. (...) Preparation of the synaptosome postsynaptic density (PSD) and presynaptic web (PSW) fractions was performed as described previously (Garside et al., 2009).\" This was also performed on human tissue.\nThe CAR antibody used for immunoblotting is not specified in the M+M" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4941" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

